      "writtenOn": "2026-04-22T09:38:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hi @ed@tanous.net RuleParameterTraits bundles HTTP-specific methods (methods(), notFound(), etc.) with privilege configuration. Non-HTTP connection types like SseSocketRule and WebSocketRule inherit only BaseRule and cannot configure privileges without pulling in all that HTTP-specific logic. By extracting privileges into PrivilegeParameterTraits, these types can inherit just the privilege API — e.g., class SseSocketRule : public BaseRule, public PrivilegeParameterTraits\u003cSseSocketRule\u003e — without unrelated HTTP routing methods. RuleParameterTraits itself then inherits PrivilegeParameterTraits to preserve existing behavior.",
